15:
Victory is mine. Your eyesight hasn't
slowed you down at allâ€”only your
reflexes themselves have dulled.
19:
I just let my guard down, that's all... I
want a rematch!
25:
The result will not change, but I will
gladly indulge you until you're
satisfied.
29: Whoa... They're so cool, huh, Eric?
38:
Heehee! I believe that puts me in the
lead.
42:
What's the matter, Alk? It's not like
you to sulk like this.
47:
Grr... I've never met a princess who
loved to talk such a big game.
55:
Do I need to remind you about what
happened two years ago? Nah... I
suppose I'd better quit while I'm
ahead.
61:
How unfair of you to bring up such a
thing!
64:
Hmph. It seems you're the type of
man who just can't put the past in
the past.
69:
There she goes again! Light, are you
hearing this? She's gonna pull a
muscle trying to one-up me like this!
72:
And besides! Do you REALLY need all
this physical strength if you're just
doing political things these days?
79: That is where you are mistaken.
82:
Have you heard the news? A former
citizen of Stratos is to wed a fiend.
86:
Huh? Wed... as in marry?! That's...
really brave of them, considering
everything that happened...
91:
The peace between our peoples is
far more established than I had
thought. But there are still those who
oppose the union.
95:
I've... heard of similar cases with the
beastfolk.
100:
No matter what world we live in,
there will always be those who are
opposed to change.
105:
As such, the threat of violence is
always looming. In this case, such a
threat has been confirmed, and I
have made preparations for an
arrest.
108:
But I do not wish to solve this conflict
with bloodshed. That is why I will
attend to the matter myself.
112:
I was completely against the idea,
but... I suppose there's no use trying
to change your mind.
116:
I want to see it through myself... to
know what I am capable of in this
moment. There's no telling what
tomorrow will bring, after all.
121:
If you need some extra muscle, I can
help out, too!
123:
That way, I can put the power I was
given by Adjudicus to good use.
127:
You held back from using it during
our match... Was it because Eric was
watching?
131:
Yeah... I know I can't keep running
away from my guilt, but... I didn't
want him to see that.
135:
None of us want you to endure that
pain alone.
137:
I want you to rely on me. And if
Shakari were here, she would say
the same.
141:
Thank you, Lilith... I can't bear the
burden as Oghir did. All I can do is
promise that I'll ask for help when I
need it.
145:
Very well... I will hold you to that
promise.
151: All right... Let us put an end to this.
154:
L... Lilith Stratos?! What the hell are
you doing here?!
157:
Surrender at once. Please, do not
throw your lives away.
160:
You traitorous wench... You were
supposed to protect our kingdom,
not let it be overrun with those filthy
fiends!
163:
I am Lilith Stratos! Daughter of the
Witch of Burning Blood, protector of
the flame!
166:
O flame of courage, burn bright!
Merge with the light of hope to
guide me through the darkness!
176:
Yeah... But it's dangerous here, kid...
You've gotta... run...
182: The fiends... they did this to me...
184:
Those bastards took everything
from me! My home... My wife! My
precious little girl!
187: My family is gone now, too...
190:
Step away from that child this
instant!
193: Don't you DARE come near me!
196:
Even from this distance, I can strike
you down.
198:
So please... step back. Don't hurt the
child.
202:
I understand why you feel sad,
mister.
205:
I really want to see my mommy
again, too. You must feel lonely... just
like me.
209:
But I have so many new friends now!
Like Miss Marly, the big fuzzy tiger
man, and Alk!
212:
They taught me that even if we are
apart, my mommy is always with
me.
218:
Please do not forget these words.
Your life is yours. You are free to
choose a new path and decide your
future.
221:
And no matter what happens,
always believe in the flame that
burns inside of your heart.
233:
Though he is still so young, the
flame in him is incredibly strong.
235:
And if there ever comes a day that
he loses his way, he can use that
flame to find his way back.
239:
It is my duty and privilege to defend
my people. To help them believe in
their flames and find their own
happiness.
243:
I came along to help you, but I
couldn't do a thing. Now I owe you
one for saving Eric, too.
248:
Who's counting? Heh, I'm beginning
to think you actually enjoy owing me
favors.
